modules.description: This module processes strings encoded in WTF-8, a superset of UTF-8 that accepts invalid Unicode encodings. It provides `fold_wtf_8` to iterate over code points, handling malformed sequences, and `add_wtf_8` to append a Unicode code point to a buffer. These functions work directly with `string` and `Buffer.t`, supporting robust handling of potentially invalid UTF-8 data in I/O or parsing scenarios.
